description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking a Band 5 Occupational Therapist to join our CARE point team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a motivated Occupational Therapist to join our Care Point Occupational Therapy team based at North Tyneside General Hospital. The successful candidate will be part of a multidisciplinary team who proactively facilitate a safe, effective and timely patient discharge and aim to prevent re-admission.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The applicant will be prepared to work weekends and bank holidays and have a valid driving license. The successful applicant must have excellent communication skills be able to work on their own initiative and as part of a team. We will provide access to reflective supervision, annual appraisals and professional development opportunities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please review job description and person specification before submitting applications.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Criteria:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Diploma or degree in OT &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;State registered with HCPC&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interest or experience in elderly, medical orthopaedics surgery and stroke rehab as well as rehabilitation and community work&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Use of evidence based practice&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Application of the O.T. process.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Use of functional assessments and activity analysis&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Desirable Criteria:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Membership of professional body&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Membership of Special Interest Group&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of working in one or more of fields listed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience of supervision of others&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using standardised assessments/outcome measures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Estelle Ferguson&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 0191 2932773&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;E-mail: Estelle.Ferguson@nhct.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 15th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
